title: Joined WayzAway!
description: Welcome to WayzAway! Why not start by inviting friends and family members so you can start to share your experiences and get ideas on places to go.

title: Pumpkins R US
description: Halloween shop, pumpkins, rides and cafe

title: RAF Museum
description: Museum dedicated to the history of aviation and the Royal Air Force. There is a playground for kids, VR rides and a gift shop.

title: Rock Up Wall Climbing
description: Indoor Wall and Tower climbing for adults and children. Has a soft play area for little kids.

title: Wyre Forest
description: Large woodland nature reserve. Great for long walks, horse riding cycling, picnic spots and has plenty of outdoor activities for adults and children. There is a go ape in the forest for zip lining, treetop challenges and treetop adventures.

title: Indoor Roller Skating
description: Large indoor room for roller blading. For adults and kids. There's a cafe nearby for food.

title: Maughold Beach
description: Located on the east of Isle of Man. Lovely cost line and scenery. Nice walk along the beach.

title: The Great Laxey Wheel
description: Historic Laxey Wheel built into the hillside above the village if Laxey. The wheel was built in 1854 to pump water. You can use the steep steps to climb to the very top of the wheel. Also includes a quick trip into the nearby old mine.

title: Glen Wyllin
description: Stopped at the beach. But also has a campsite

title: Woodgate Valley Country Park
description: Rural park with Brook running through the middle. Great for long walks and horse riding. There is an apple orchard for apple picking. And a children's playground. The park also has a small farm in the middle with pigs, goats, chickens and cows.

title: Manor Farm Fruits
description: Fruit picking. A wide range if fruits available to pick in the summer. There's a playground and bouncy castle for kids. Outdoor BBQ and cafe.

title: Claremont Landscape Garden
description: Grade 1 listed garden. Great nature walk, woodland and beautiful lake. There's a playground and cafe on site. Part of the National Trust.

title: Gheluvelt Park
description: Public park with plenty of space for outdoor activities, walking and picnics. There is a splash park in the summer and playground for kids. There is a small shop that sells drinks and refreshments and tennis courts.

title: Habberley Trail
description:
Outdoor nature adventure and walk. Includes plenty of fun outdoor activities such as zip lining, bouncy castles for kids, large slides, rides and more
There's a small cafe that sells food and drinks.

title: Dudley Canal and Caverns
description: Boat tour of black country canal and tunnel networks. We did this around Easther, hence the Easter theme.

title: Sheldon Country Park
description: Country Park and Farm with children's play area and walking path that leads to the airport.

title: Basel
description: Holiday to Basel

title: Wrens Nest National Nature Reserve
description: Geological location. Circular walk around large limestone outcrop.

title: Center Parcs
description: Wildlife sanctuary on the edge of Lake District. Holiday Park with wide variety of indoor and outdoor activities for adults and kids.

title: Sea Life Centre
description: Large Aquarium with displays of sea creatures

title: Ash End Farm
description: Farm with tractor wides, animal feeding and large play area for kids

title: Playa Del Carmen
description: Resort town on southeast cost of Lanzarote. Plenty of sandy beaches, restaurants and long walks in the warm weather.

title: Brueton Park Lake
description: Big Park with great easy pathway for long walks and cycling. Play area for children.

title: Highbury Park and Highbury Hall
description: Park with plenty of woodland and an historic house. Large open spaces for the dog to run around.

title: Coombe Abbey
description: Large park with children play area, independent shops, cafe, long walks and outdoor activites. There's a large historic house in the park with  maze garden and lake.

title: Apple Orchard
description: Apple picking located in the orchard in Woodgate Valley Park.

title: Nature Walk
description: Long walk through woodlands and farmland.

title: Clent Hills
description: Countryside haven that is part of the National Trust

title: Manor Farm Fruits
description: Fruit picking farm

title: Lickey Hills
description: Lickey Hills is a large country park. But this was a walk through the wooded section of the park.

title: Atwell Farm
description: Met and fed animals. Enjoyed indoor and outdoor play areas, a jumping pillow and some art and craft

title: Cannon Hill
description: Large park in the middle of Birmingham. Great for walks and there's a play area for children.

title: Charlecote Park
description: A historic grand 16th century country house surrounded by a deer park on the banks of River Avon.

title: Villa el Palacete
description: Spent 5 nights in a large villa in Lanzarote for mums 60th birthday.

title: Packwood House
description: Tutor manor house in Solihull. Owned by the National Trust and known for its garden of yews.

title: Hanbury Hall
description: Large 18th century stately home surrounded by large open fields and gardens.

title: Adventure Mini Golf
description: 18 holes indoor mini adenture golf.

title: Wightwick Manor
description: A Victorian Manor owned by the National Trust. The house is surrounded by woodland, gardens. There is a woodland play area in the woods.

title: Baddesley Clinton
description: A moated Manor house originating from the 13th century. Located in the middle of the Forest of Arden and owned by the National Trust.

title: Upton House & Garden
description: Historic house built on the site of hamlet of Upton. The house and gardens are owned by the National Trust.

title: Cannon Hill Park
description: Large park in middle of Birmingham with excellent pathway for walking, running and cycling. Plenty of open grass area for children and dogs to play.

title: Berrington Hall
description: A country house owned by the National Trust. A Georgian neoclassical mansion by Henry Rolland built in 1778. It's surrounded by browns final landscape and gardens.

title: Rush Trampoline
description: A large trampoline park for children. Plenty of fun and unique activities.

title: Croome Park
description: Mid 18th-century mansion surrounded by extensive landscaped parkland at Croome D'Abitot. The property is owned by the National Trust.

title: Hippodrome & Las Iguanas
description: Ballet show for children and restaurant after.

title: Hanbury Hall
description: 18 Century House owned by the National Trust

title: Play 360
description: Soft play and Party venue. The center also has rides for kids and plenty of toys for kids.

title: Coughton Court
description: Grade I English Tudor country house owned by the National Trust. The house holds a variety of Catholic treasures and is set in a beautiful garden.

title: Baggeridge Country Park
description: Country Park with acres of open space for walking and cycling. There's a children play area, open grass to play and a high rope adventure area.

title: Old Hall
description: One of the hiding places of Charles II during his escape to France following defeat at Battle of Worcester in 1651. We visited around easther and took part in the egg hunt. The house is surrounded by woodland and a curated garden. We played games from Elizabethan times in the garden.

title: Kingsbury Water Park
description: The park has fifteen lakes and situated in over 600 acres of land. There is a miniature railway to ride, a children's play area, you can hire bikes and plenty of outdoor activities for children.

title: Upper Bittell Reservoir
description: Wall around the Bittell Reservoir in Cofton.

title: Lido in Cirencester
description: Visited the Lido in Cirencester. Then explored the Cotsworld town before stopping at a pub for dinner.

title: Earlswood Lakes
description: Man made reservoirs in Solihull. Great for a nice walk around the lake.

title: Chasewater Country Park
description: Large park with a walking path around a beautiful lake. Includes a lakeside cafe, art and craft, activities like wake-boarding, sailing and water skiing. There were also trampoline for kids and a play area.

title: City Walk
description: Day out in Birmingham

title: Mount Pilatus
description: Took a gondola up the mountain. Then a train down. Up in the moutain we explored the tunnels and took in the sights.

title: Colmar
description: Day trip from Basel to the markets in Colmar

title: Live Peter Rabbit Show
description: Live play of Peter Rabbit in the park

title: Basel Zoo
description: Switzerland's biggest zoo.

title: Milkshake Live
description: Live show of Milkshake

title: Charlecote Park
description: 16th century house surrounded by a deer park.

title: Packwood House
description: Tudor Manor house sorrounded yew garden owned by thr National Trust.

title: Jimmy Spices
description: Global buffet restaurant on Broad Street.

title: Basel Munster
description: Originally a Catholic cathedral. Now a Reformed Protestant church. We were able to climb the towers all the way to the top.

title: Shustoke Reservoir
description: 9km Circular walking path around Shustoke Reservoir with beautiful views and wildlife.

title: Chinese New Year
description: Chinese New year celebrations in the Chinese Quarter. Live shows, performances and celebrations.

title: Woodgate Valley Park
description: Circular walk through the woods and around a horse field.

title: Biddulph Grange Garden
description: National Trust landscaped garden.

title: The Falconry Centre
description: Located in Webbs Garden Centre. A lovely little place with beautiful birds.

title: Witley Court and Gardens
description:
Magnificent house built in 17th century. But now lays in ruin after a fire in 1937.

Beautiful gardens, walking path, tree house, wobbly Bridge and Great Witley Chruch.

title: Mary Stevens Park
description: Public park opened in 1931. Large grass fields ideal for play and dogs. There's a play area for children and a cafe.

title: Sedgley Adventure Golf
description: Outdoor mini golf

title: Black Country Museum
description: An open-air museum of rebuilt historic buildings in Dudley. Museum staff role play as characters from the late 19th and early 20th century. The museum contains many of the tools and equipments used during mining and you can visit one of the mines in a guided tour. The village and shops around the mines have been rebuilt to match early 20th century lifestyle.

title: Kenilworth Castle and Elizabeth Ian Garden
description:
Used to be one of the country's most formidable fortresses. Robert Dudley later transformed it into a spectacular Palace in order to impress Queen Elizabeth I.

We partook in an Easter egg hunt, watched a live medieval show and walked around the ruined castle. There is a cafe and shop on site.

There is also a museum with information detailing the relationship between Elizabeth I and Robert Dudley.

title: Atwell Farm Park
description: Feed farm animals, see a wide variety of animals and large insects. There are some indoor rides and soft play. Plus giant outdoor jumping pillows.

title: Ryton Pools Country Park
description:
Plenty of area to explore. Can walk or hire a bike. There is a woodland to play in and a lake.

The park has more than one children's play area and a cafe.

The park covers 100 acres of land and the flat walking path makes it easy for buggies.

title: Kings Heath Park
description:
Large Park with a circular path around a grass area. Ideal for playing and cycling. Has a couple of children's play area. Great for dog walking. There is a very small pond in some woodlands and a small cafe.

Zoe learnt to ride her bike here.

title: Treasure Island
description: Soft play indoor for kids. Includes an indoor trampoline park.

title: The Sound
description: Lovely spot on the very edge of the Island to see the seals and other wildlife. Can spot the Calf of Man here and have something to eat at the cafe.

title: Peel Castle & Beach
description: Visited the historic Peel castle and walked along the beautiful beach. Built some sand castle and waded in the sea.

title: Douglas Beach
description: Enjoyed the beach at Douglas and stopped at a small ice cream cafe.

title: Day Out in Birmingham & Restaurant
description: Explored Birmingham Central. Visited Europe's biggest libary and eat at Zizi

title: Wildlife Conservation Park
description: A small zoo in Birmingham with a wide variety of animals. Theres a small restaurant, a shop and a children's play area on site.

title: Day Trip To Weymouth Beach
description: Day trip to Weymouth beach. Enjoyed rides on the beach and various games. Attended an arcade with family games and eat at a sea side restaurant.

title: Beacons Park
description: 70 acres of beautiful open space. There is a large children's play area and rides for kids to enjoy. The park also has outdoor mini golf and walking path. There is a small cafe in the park.

title: Abbey Park
description: An open park with a splash park. The park has a children's play area, basket ball court, sand pit and an historic church at the other end.

title: St Nicholas Park
description: Large open park with rides, a beautiful stream, large lake for water activities a splash pool and more

title: Grange Park and Playground
description: Large open park with playground. The park also has a small cafe which sells hot drinks, ice cream, deserts and other snacks. There are toilets available.

title: Leamington RFC Bonfire Night
description:
Fireworks display at Leamington Spa Rugby Club. There were rides for the kids, food stand and an indoor bar to sit.

Toilets were available and everyone had a great view of the fireworks.

The display itself was about 20 mins. Entry was Â£20 for family of 4 (Two adults and 2 kids).

title: West Midland Zoo
description: Safari and Leisure Park is a safari park located in Bewdley in Worcestershire, England.

title: Worcester Park Festival
description: Great day out with Mike and Sarah. Music was great, really enjoyed myself. Should've bought a bigger tent though.

title: British Museum
description: Day out in London visiting the sites

description: It was a nice day, so John and I took the kids to the park to enjoy the sunshine and some icecream

title: Lea Valley Zoo
description:

The kids ended the day in the zoo playground.

description: Weekend away with John and the kids at Weymouth

title: Glen Wyllin
description:
A glen in the Isle of Man. It is one of the officially-listed Manx National Glens. The Glen Wyllin Pleasure Grounds are owned by the Isle of Man Railway whose line crossed the valley by means of a viaduct.

The site is popular amongst campers but we stopped for a couple of hours at the beach located here. It was a warm evening with cool breeze. We also caught a glimpse of a couple of dolphins that swam close to the shore.

title: Real Midlands 5 - 1 Camden
description:
First game of the 2024 season ended with a disappointing loss.

Team was largely meeting for the first time with so many not available for pre-season.

Real Midlands started off shaky but scored first. Camden equalised after a through ball to Tom from Will. However Real Midlands ended up dominating the whole game scoring 4 more goals to get a comfortable victory.

We shot ourselves in the foot, with three of the goals against us coming from keeper mistakes and one other from failure to clear the ball. Karim had a couple chances which he would have buried on another day, he's rustiness is understood given it was his first league game in a year and had only played 1 pre season game prior to this.
Other than that we didn't really threaten Real Midlands and the game was comfortable for them.

Camden Squad
Emad

Will 
Laye
Badri
Tom
Maz
Karim

Sub
Deano
Luke

Goals: Tom assisted by Will

title: Blaze 9 - 2 Camden
description:
Festival Cup

We started strong by scoring  early to go 1 nil up from a converted penalty by Karim. But a defensive mistake from Khalid led to an equaliser. Karim scored another goal from a Maz cross to make it 2-1. Karim took the ball down well from the cross and put it into the bottom corner with a clever finish.

From then on Camden collapse. Mistake after mistake from Camden resulted on easy goals against us.

It didn't help that we started arguing amongst each other and by second half the game plan went out the window. Birmingham Blaze goal keeper was sent off for handballing outside the area. A mistake from the ref as this isn't a red card offence. However, even with 10 men Blaze went on to score 5 more goals against us.

Karim, won a penalty assisted by Tom
Karim assisted by Maz

title: Bizspace 1 - 1 Camden
description:
A much better performance. We switched to 3 at the back to deal with Bizspace long balls. The formation worked well.

The game was tight and remained goaless at half time. Will and Sam worked hard as a two in midfield and as the game went on Camden started to take control. We scored first early in the second half after a great ball from Tom to Hansu and he cleverly laid it off to Badri who lobbed the keeper with a shot from outside the area.

Bizspace came back into the game last 15 mins. And again we conceded from a set piece after we failed to follow the second ball.

Goal: Badri assisted by Hansu

Camden scored first but Villa Tavern got a goal back. With both sides getting plenty of chances both teams were 3 all with only a few minutes left.

However, after a great cross from Adrian, Badri slammed home the winner with a great header in the last 2 minutes. We were able to hold out for a great win.

title: Wanderers 3 - 3 Camden
description:
A decent result against on of the better teams in the league.

We went 2 nil down in the first 15 minutes.

We started with 5 at the back but after a change of formation by putting an extra man in midfield things improved. We also realised that playing more direct to exploit their weak defence.

Karim managed to get us a goal back, then we unfortunately went 3 - 1 down. However after another change of formation in the second half going 442. We dominated the game and put the game back to 3 all after a great finish from Tom.

Wanderers did get a last minute penalty after their player tripped over his own foot. But with the last kick of the game their taker skied the penalty.

title: Beaufort Arms 2 - 4 Camden
description:
Festival and Sutton Inter cup

We started poorly with a goal conceded in first 5 minutes  when keeper misjudged a long ball and it bounced over him into the goal.

But we recovered well and after a shaky start Karim scored from a Badri through ball.

We got lucky with a Jerome goal that was offside to make it 2 - 1.

Then another piece of luck when referee gave a corner to Camden that was a goal kick. Sam scored from the preceding corner to make it 3 - 1.

Camden continued to dominate until Jerome made it 4 - 1 in second half. Beaufort made it interesting by getting one back. But Camden had several chances to score even more and remained in control for the remainder of the game.

Sam in midfield put in a man of the match performance with his energy and closing down.

title: Camden vs North West Spartans
description:
Sam Leach Memorial Cup

Probably one of the worst game of the season for Camden. Although we scored first we never really had control of the game.

First goal was an assist from Tom to Jerome. However after a mistake from one of our defenders and failure to deal with their runner they equalised. Spartans took the lead early in 1st half after Deano and David failed to communicate when going for an header which meant the ball dropped for their player to put in the bottom corner.

We managed to equalise from a Doyin header - corner from Tom.

The game went into penalties, although they missed their first after a good save from Adrian. We also missed our first. Unfortunately Deano the 5th taker missed his pen and Spartans go through to next round.

Camden never really had control of the game and in truth deserved to lose.

Goal

Jerome assisted by Tom
Doyin assisted by Tom

Motm - Hansu

title: Villa Tavern vs Camden
description:
League Game

Started slow, went 2 nil down. We made a tactical change in midfield and things changed. Karim scored to get us to 2-1 before tom equalised and Karim scored to make it 3-2 by half time.

We came out and scored early with Karim completing his hatrick. Unfortunately Karim suffered a bad tackle and had to come off.

However, we continued with our momentum to score 2 more.

Camden suffered a temporary glitch which resulted in Villa Tavern pulling the score back to 5-3. But Camden carried on to finish the game strongly by scoring 3 more goals.

Goal scorers and Assist

Karim assisted by Tom
Karim assisted by Hansu
Karim assisted by Tom
Tom assisted by Doyin
Sam O assisted by Adrian
Adrian penalty won by Sam O
Will assisted by Badri
Sam O

title: Camden vs Wanderers
description:
Camden 2:0 Wanderers

League Game

A great win against closest rivals for 3rd spot.

After 3 seasons playing each other Camden registered their first win against Wanderers 

The game was tight but we were the slightly better team for the most part.

First goal came from a great cross from Karim to Sam. 

Second goal came from Sam.pressing on the defender to rob him off the ball before slotting into the bottom corner.

The defence was in great form and kept their attackers at bay for the most part.

Goal scorers: Sam 0 x 2

Motm: Sam O and Doyin
